    <!-- Consent dialog (first-run telemetry opt-in, DRAFT, three tiers) -->
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Title">Help improve ClickyKeys?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Header">Help improve ClickyKeys?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Body">We'd like to collect anonymous usage statistics to understand how ClickyKeys is used and prioritize what to build next. This is entirely optional, never affects how the app works, and you can change your choice at any time.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_KeyloggerAssurance">ClickyKeys is not a keylogger. Whichever option you pick below — even Full — it never records what you type, your passwords, clipboard contents, or which specific keys you press or click. Keeping you safe matters to this project, and the source code is fully open so you (or anyone else) can check that for yourself — no need to just take our word for it. See it on GitHub:</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_FullTitle">Full — usage &amp; feature statistics</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_FullBody">Everything in Basic, plus how features are configured and used: panel layout and grid size, which display modes are on (transparent, rainbow background), whether colors/fonts/shortcuts were customized, gamepad settings, and aggregate key/mouse/uptime counts. Never your panel labels, exact colors, exact shortcut keys, or anything you typed.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_BasicTitle">Basic — basic usage &amp; anonymous identity</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_BasicBody">A randomly generated ID (not tied to you or your PC), the app version, your OS version, your interface language, plus your combined key press count and total uptime.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_NoneTitle">None — don't collect anything</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_NoneBody">Nothing is sent to any server. You can turn statistics on later from Settings → Data Collection if you change your mind.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_Footnote">You can change your choice at any time in Settings → Data Collection.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Consent_PrivacyPolicyLink">Read the full privacy policy</sys:String>

